in rome , pope john paul launched the countdown to the year 2000 today by reviving a catholic tradition from the middle ages . reporter : in a three-hour ceremony this morning , the pope declared 2000 will be a holy year . during that year , catholics will be ablto earn indulgences by doing good works . an indulgence eliminates punishment for sin , speeding entry into heaven . in the 16th century , indulgences got a bad name , because the church sold them . they were part of the reason martin luther broke away and formed the protestant church . but theologians say the 21st century indulgence is different . an indulgence in the way he 's using it , is not as a means for gathering money for the church , but rather as a means of enhancing your soul . according to the papal edict , catholics can earn indulgences by giving up cigarettes or alcohol for a day , or by visiting someone in prison or in the hospital . 